01:10:53.015 --> 01:10:54.530
is a stochastic variable.

01:10:54.530 --> 01:10:56.420
It varies from run to run.

01:10:56.420 --> 01:10:59.720
So you want to say--

01:10:59.720 --> 01:11:01.550
you want to make
a claim about what

01:11:01.550 --> 01:11:03.650
the typical running time is.

01:11:03.650 --> 01:11:06.230
But then you have to have
some recovery time to account

01:11:06.230 --> 01:11:08.010
for anything later than that.

01:11:08.010 --> 01:11:10.400
And you recognize-- it's
a way of recognizing

01:11:10.400 --> 01:11:12.800
that these running
times are stochastic.

01:11:12.800 --> 01:11:17.810
